1. install R : sudo apt-get install r-cran-rjava

2. add these to ~/.bashrc :
	WARNING: Folder may differ for different machines(not necessarily "/usr/lib/R"), chech out the R repository. 
	export R_HOME=/usr/lib/R
	export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=/usr/lib/R/site-library/rJava/jri/
	
	
http://binfalse.de/2011/02/talking-r-through-java/
http://autofei.wordpress.com/2010/08/04/getting-rjavajri-to-work-it-is-painful/